WEBVTT

00:00:03.759 --> 00:00:16.760
Peace must be sought above all our military forces are committed to peace. We have chosen peace. Our wish, our prayer is for peace.

00:00:16.760 --> 00:00:25.859
We yearn for peace. We pray for peace.

00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:36.079
For thousands of years humans have tried to find peace.

00:00:36.079 --> 00:00:49.960
Peace is individuals. Peace is families. Peace for the entire human race.

00:00:49.960 --> 00:00:59.539
We want to lay the foundation of peace for generations to come. We want to do the hard work now.

00:00:59.539 --> 00:01:06.620
So our children and our grandchildren can grow up in a peaceful world.

00:01:06.620 --> 00:01:20.540
The future we want, opportunity and security for our families, a rising standard of living, a sustainable, peaceful planet for our kids.

00:01:20.540 --> 00:01:27.780
All that is within our reach.

00:01:27.780 --> 00:02:00.859
Yet despite humans' best efforts, peace has been elusive.

00:02:00.859 --> 00:02:11.860
For millenniums, rulers and governments have tried to achieve peace through treaties, resolutions, summits and ironically war.

00:02:11.860 --> 00:02:26.110
Our peace as humans is more fragile than ever.

00:02:26.110 --> 00:02:33.110
Man's efforts to bring about lasting peace have failed. Time and time again.

00:02:33.110 --> 00:02:44.110
This isn't surprising to us. Jeremiah 1023 tells us it does not belong to man to direct his step.

00:02:44.110 --> 00:02:49.110
Humans were simply not designed to rule themselves.

00:02:49.110 --> 00:03:00.110
Good health, safety, overall well-being, these are becoming harder to find as we move further into what the Bible refers to as the last days.

00:03:00.110 --> 00:03:06.110
As long as human rule continues, disunity will continue.

00:03:06.110 --> 00:03:11.110
It's true that global peace cannot be obtained by human efforts alone.

00:03:11.110 --> 00:03:16.110
But those who are close to God can find peace of mind right now.

00:03:16.110 --> 00:03:19.110
Isaiah 48 17 and 18 says,

00:03:19.110 --> 00:03:22.110
I Jehovah, am your God.

00:03:22.110 --> 00:03:28.110
The one teaching you to benefit yourself, the one guiding you and the way you should walk.

00:03:28.110 --> 00:03:32.110
If only you would pay attention to my commandments.

00:03:32.110 --> 00:03:36.110
Then your peace would become just like a river.

00:03:36.110 --> 00:03:43.110
It's only Jehovah who has the ability to guide humans to real lasting peace.

00:03:43.110 --> 00:03:47.110
He promises he will bring this about until this happens.

00:03:47.110 --> 00:03:53.110
Jehovah continues to provide ways for us to experience peace now. How does he do that?

00:03:53.110 --> 00:03:58.110
By giving us the peace of God, that surpasses all understanding.

00:03:58.110 --> 00:04:15.479
We aren't the only ones whose peace has been challenged.

00:04:15.479 --> 00:04:23.480
God's Word is filled with accounts of faithful servants, whose peace was challenged by the dominating forces of their day.

00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:26.480
As we study and meditate on these accounts,

00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:34.480
the lessons we learn from them help us to trust in Jehovah as he guides us to peace.

00:04:34.480 --> 00:04:38.480
Understanding how these accounts related Jehovah's purpose to bring peace,

00:04:38.480 --> 00:04:43.480
by means of his Messianic Kingdom, gives us confidence that his purpose never fails

00:04:43.480 --> 00:04:47.480
and he will support and guide us on into the future.

00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:52.480
One of Jehovah's prophets who learned this lesson firsthand was Jonah.

00:04:53.480 --> 00:04:57.480
Jonah lived in the 9th century BCE.

00:04:57.480 --> 00:05:02.480
Jehovah signed Jonah to go to Nineveh, a city of the Assyrian Empire.

00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:09.480
Based on what he knew about Nineveh, Jonah considered this to be an intimidating and threatening assignment.

00:05:09.480 --> 00:05:18.480
The Assyrians are known as fierce warriors, and Nineveh itself is later described as a city of bloodshed.

00:05:18.480 --> 00:05:27.480
So you can understand Jonah's trepidation when Jehovah asks him to proclaim a judgment message against this imposing city and its pagan inhabitants.

00:05:27.480 --> 00:05:40.220
In an attempt to find peace, Jonah decides to go far away from Nineveh and boards a boat headed for Tarshish.

00:05:40.220 --> 00:05:48.730
Tarshish is generally associated with modern-day Spain.

00:05:48.730 --> 00:05:53.730
So from Israel, this is the complete opposite direction of Nineveh.

00:05:57.639 --> 00:06:06.589
Jonah found anything but peace.

00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:27.040
Now this was no ordinary storm.

00:06:27.040 --> 00:06:31.040
It was so severe that the ship was in danger of being wrecked.

00:06:35.910 --> 00:06:46.620
The crew cried out to their gods, but Jonah knew the true source of the storm.

00:06:46.620 --> 00:06:51.620
And now he accepts personal responsibility for the situation.

00:06:51.620 --> 00:06:56.620
Lift me up and throw me into the sea, and the sea will calm down for you.

00:06:56.620 --> 00:07:03.259
But I know that it's because of me that this violent storm has come upon you.

00:07:03.259 --> 00:07:09.259
Can you imagine the courage it took for Jonah to make this request?

00:07:09.259 --> 00:07:27.779
He had no way of knowing if Jehovah would save him, but he did not want others to perish on his account.

00:07:27.779 --> 00:07:31.779
In his mercy, Jehovah spares Jonah's life.

00:07:31.779 --> 00:07:33.779
I must alive.

00:07:33.779 --> 00:07:36.779
What will be called of me?

00:07:36.779 --> 00:07:44.779
When faced with a difficult assignment, Jonah got up to run away from Jehovah to Tarshish.

00:07:44.779 --> 00:07:50.779
Jonah's conscience had to bother him. He had to be questioning his decision.

00:07:50.779 --> 00:07:55.779
He tried to take matters into his own hands, tried to find his own peace.

00:07:55.779 --> 00:08:00.779
Where does he find himself in the belly of a fish?

00:08:00.779 --> 00:08:03.779
Yet he calls to Jehovah in a moment of despair.

00:08:03.779 --> 00:08:15.339
Oh, Jehovah, out of the depths of the grave, I cry to you for help.

00:08:15.339 --> 00:08:24.089
He's here, my voice. When I abound, I will pay.

00:08:24.089 --> 00:08:34.409
Jonah could have reasoned that this was the end of his assignment as Jehovah's Prophet.

00:08:34.409 --> 00:08:38.409
After all, he did disobey direction.

00:08:39.409 --> 00:08:44.409
So likely he was surprised to hear the word of Jehovah come to him a second time.

00:08:44.409 --> 00:09:05.779
Go to Nine of the Great City and proclaim to her the message that I tell you.

00:09:05.779 --> 00:09:09.779
Yes. Yes. Thank you.

00:09:09.779 --> 00:09:23.919
At first, Jonah trusted in himself and didn't understand that Jehovah would protect him from the violent assyrians.

00:09:23.919 --> 00:09:26.919
